-- Spain’s Rajoy Predicts Strikes on Labor Reform, Economista Says
-- B y   S h a r o n   S m y t h
-- 2012-01-31T06:19:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-31/spain-s-rajoy-predicts-strikes-on-labor-reform-economista-says.html
Spanish Prime Minister  Mariano Rajoy 
expects forthcoming labor reforms in  Spain  to provoke strikes
among workers,  El Economista  reported.  Before the start of a European Union summit in Brussels
yesterday Rajoy, while speaking to his Finnish counterpart Jyrki Katainen and unaware that his microphone was turned on, said
that reform would “cost him a strike”, El Economista said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sharon Smyth in  Madrid   at 
 ssmyth2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
